Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Trim and halve @Brussels Sprouts{8%ounce}. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Arrange cut sides down on one side of baking sheet. Roast until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes} total.

Meanwhile, peel and dice @sweet potatoes{2} into ½-inch cubes. Place in a large #pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until easily pierced by a fork, ~{10-15%minutes}. Drain and return to pot.

Pat @chicken breasts{12%ounce}(boneless and skinless) dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt, pepper, and @smoky cinnamon paprika spice{1/2%tablespoon} (save the rest for another use). Heat a drizzle of oil in a medium pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until lightly browned but not cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} per side. Turn off heat. Transfer to baking sheet with Brussels sprouts, pushing sprouts toward one side. Roast until cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes}.

> TIP: If chicken is done before Brussels sprouts, remove from sheet and return sprouts to oven.

Add @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @currant jam{2%tablespoon}, and ¼ cup water to pan used to cook chicken. Cook over medium-low heat, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan, until slightly reduced, ~{3-4%minutes}. Turn off heat; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

Meanwhile, heat pot with sweet potatoes over low heat. Using a #potato masher{} or #fork{}, mash sweet potatoes with @sour cream{2%tablespoon} and @butter{1%tablespoon}. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide sweet potatoes, Brussels sprouts, and chicken between plates. Drizzle chicken with sauce.